modules.description: This module implements an M-tree data structure for efficient similarity searches in metric spaces. It supports operations such as insertion of points, range queries within a given radius, and tree restructuring through promotion, partitioning, and splitting nodes. The core data types include tree nodes and objects representing data points, with concrete use cases in nearest neighbor searches and clustering algorithms.

Implements an M-tree data structure for efficient similarity searches in metric spaces. Supports insertion of points, range queries within a specified radius, and iteration over tree contents, working directly with metric data points and their distance calculations. Useful for nearest neighbor searches and clustering algorithms where distance-based organization is critical.
